{"type":"message","id":"d99de88a","parentId":"f5c84dd2","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:24:05.184Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand better. The user is talking about the openclaw-tui setup where they enter credentials (Confluence API key, email, API token, bot token). The issue is that after entering the credentials, the system still shows the user's (Lead's) data instead of the new user's data.\n\nThis sounds like the issue might be with the Confluence MCP configuration. The Confluence MCP tools are configured per workspace in the openclaw config. When a new user sets up, they might be entering their own Confluence credentials, but the MCP tools might still be pointing to the Lead's Confluence account.\n\nLet me check the openclaw.json more carefully and also look at the confluence configs.\n\n\nI need to see how the confluence MCP credentials are actually stored in the configuration to understand where the disconnect is happening.","thinkingSignature":"a0f93e3942d91a95c432e6b9f88c943a9926cc007061a50f10d037412a1ed333"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sgca1rqfy3o2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d.get('mcpServers', d.get('mcp', {})), indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null | head -60"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sgca1rqfy3o2_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/configs/team-dev.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d.get('mcpServers', d.get('mcp', {})), indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":835,"output":352,"cacheRead":23392,"cacheWrite":1054,"totalTokens":25633,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":