{"type":"message","id":"4c045b09","parentId":"4f350cd0","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:27:08.361Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, syntax is fine. The diff includes both my fix and other changes from the previous session. Let me commit this with a clear message.","thinkingSignature":"ff0ae3b35b3e3c235e5064f2158ba1b022225f3073e8c2ba8cd72ac509315091"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5mht5guy1y8o_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review && git commit -m \"fix(setup): apply all 3 Confluence fields (url+email+token) to mcpServers\n\nRoot cause: applyCredentials only set CONF_TOKEN but left CONF_BASE_URL\nand CONF_USERNAME empty — so MCP server logged in as Lead's account\nregardless of what the new user entered.\n\nFix:\n- collectCredentials now prompts for confUrl + confEmail + confToken\n  (3 separate questions instead of 1)\n- applyCredentials applies all 3 to every confluence-* MCP server\n- Uses config.mcpServers (camelCase) matching openclaw.json schema\n- Bot token fix: channels.telegram.bots (not accounts.telegram.bots)\n\nFixes: new user enters Confluence credentials but system still uses\nLead's account data\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":144,"output":230,"cacheRead":43029,"cacheWrite":4773,"totalTokens":48176,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776256021282,"responseId":"062eb71616eafacdde59f1edd4e78b54"}}
