{"type":"message","id":"cdf0be9e","parentId":"046f8c8c","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:29:50.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. The `install.sh` already supports `--yes` flag (line 448), but the `install.sh` itself needs to pass `--yes` to `bin/ahv-setup.js` when stdin is not a TTY (piped).\n\nLet me check how `install.sh` calls `bin/ahv-setup.js`:","thinkingSignature":"a44858559701f6738d790f19ae5138130bd194091eecf8d5a7d02f1d22aacae5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0qepzqq4tb1p_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"ahv-setup\\|node bin\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/install.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":319,"output":130,"cacheRead":48224,"cacheWrite":270,"totalTokens":48943,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776256186716,"responseId":"062eb7bb7c10bde6f45711eb38c825aa"}}
