{"type":"message","id":"09fbb633","parentId":"ef668d9c","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:29:58.561Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The install.sh calls `bin/ahv-setup.js` without `--yes`, even when running via pipe. The fix should be:\n\n1. When stdin is NOT a TTY (piped via curl | bash), auto-add `--yes`\n2. This should be done in install.sh before calling ahv-setup.js\n\nThe fix: in install.sh, detect if stdin is a TTY. If not, add `--yes` to the ahv-setup.js call.\n\nAlso, let me check if there's a specific issue with the team selection prompt. When running via pipe, even `--yes` won't help for the team selection (it's required). Users would need to pass `--team dev` explicitly.\n \nSo the core issue is that users running `curl | bash` need to either pass `--team` upfront or have the script auto-skip to non-interactive mode when stdin isn't available.","thinkingSignature":"4d12a1cd8144bb3b2270ddfd5e3630f039a113ee993cdf5a36a379b7bfb42c5f"},{"type":"text","text":"Đúng rồi. Khi chạy `curl ... | bash`, stdin bị curl chiếm → inquirer không đọc được `y/n` → treo.\n\nFix: `install.sh` phải detect piped mode và tự thêm `--yes`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ae3qlnqlra96_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/install.sh","offset":75,"limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":155,"output":308,"cacheRead":48176,"cacheWrite":642,"totalTokens":49281,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776256191078,"responseId":"062eb7c0a9124297397a22e1b904f2b0"}}
