{"type":"message","id":"f3e3760e","parentId":"955bc12c","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:30:19.717Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `--yes` flag only affects the confirmation prompts after team selection, but the team selection itself (line 457) is NOT skipped by `--yes`. This means:1. User runs `curl ... | bash` without `--team` → script prompts for team → stdin gone → hangs\n2. User runs `curl ... | bash -- dev` → team selected → confirmations skipped → works\n\nSo I need to also make team selection skippable. The best fix: if `--team` is not provided AND stdin is not a TTY, default to \"dev\" (or show usage error).\n\nLet me check the current team selection logic more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"d77d0027d6325ed2e140762ceed17b2a1f878c71c701dbd91b33951ce0fe358b"},{"type":"text","text":"\nCần fix thêm: team selection prompt vẫn chạy dù có `--yes`. Khi pipe mà không truyền `--team`, script sẽ treo:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0dlsskw7vh1r_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js","offset":436,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":209,"output":247,"cacheRead":49760,"cacheWrite":314,"totalTokens":50530,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776256212834,"responseId":"062eb7d537b1d0c81367a00ddf3e5c85"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f69bc8c","parentId":"f3e3760e","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:30:19.831Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0dlsskw7vh1r_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  const args = process.argv.slice(2);\n  let teamArg = null;\n  let skipIntro = false;\n\n  for (const arg of args) {\n    if (arg === \"--team\" || arg === \"-t\") {\n      const idx = args.indexOf(arg);\n      teamArg = args[idx + 1];\n    }\n    if (arg.startsWith(\"--team=\")) {\n      teamArg = arg.replace(\"--team=\", \"\");\n    }\n    if (arg === \"--yes\" || arg === \"-y\") skipIntro = true;\n  }\n\n  // Check prereqs\n  checkPrereqs();\n\n  // Select team\n  let team = teamArg;\n  if (!team) {\n    const { selected } = await inquirer.prompt([\n      {\n        type: \"list\",\n        name: \"selected\",\n        message: chalk.cyan(\"Chọn team của bạn:\"),\n        choices: [\n          { name: \"👨‍💻 Team Dev  — Backend, Frontend, DevOps, Architecture\", value: \"dev\" },\n          { name: \"📊 Team BA   — Product Owner, Strategy, Epic Design\", value: \"ba\" },\n          { name: \"🧪 Team QA  — QA, Playwright, Security, Performance\", value: \"qa\" }\n        ]\n      }\n    ]);\n    team = selected;\n  }\n\n  if (!TEAMS[team]) {\n    console.log(chalk.red(`\\n❌ Team không hợp lệ: ${team}`));\n    console.log(chalk.dim(\"Chọn: dev | ba | qa\\n\"));\n    process.exit(1);\n\n[83 more lines in file. Use offset=476 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776256219789}}
{"type":"message","id":"8572ac59","parentId":"1f69bc8c","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:30:30.088Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to change the team selection logic to default to \"dev\" when no team is specified AND skipIntro is true (piped mode). The fix:\n\n```javascript\n// Select team\nlet team = teamArg;\nif (!team) {\n  if (skipIntro) {\n    team = \"dev\";\n    console.log(chalk.dim(\"No --team specified in piped mode → defaulting to dev\"));\n  } else {\n    const { selected } = await inquirer.prompt([...]);\n    team = selected;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis way:- Interactive mode: prompts for team selection- Piped mode with `--yes`: defaults to \"dev\"\n\n\n- Piped mode with explicit `--team`: uses specified team\n\nNow I need to update install.sh so it detects non-TTY input and automatically defaults to the \"dev\" team when none is specified.","thinkingSignature":"3053c77da7c444de77240b4a2bf310c4a15594334f6b110ddd866dcf26541da0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_574g3r5qlt6d_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js","edits":[{"oldText":"  // Select team\n  let team = teamArg;\n  if (!team) {\n    const { selected } = await inquirer.prompt([\n      {\n        type: \"list\",\n        name: \"selected\",\n        message: chalk.cyan(\"Chọn team của bạn:\"),\n        choices: [\n          { name: \"👨💻 Team Dev  — Backend, Frontend, DevOps, Architecture\", value: \"dev\" },\n          { name: \"📊 Team BA   — Product Owner, Strategy, Epic Design\", value: \"ba\" },\n          { name: \"🧪 Team QA  — QA, Playwright, Security, Performance\", value: \"qa\" }\n        ]\n      }\n    ]);\n    team = selected;\n  }","newText":"  // Select team — auto-default to dev when stdin is not a TTY (piped mode)\n  let team = teamArg;\n  if (!team) {\n    if (skipIntro) {\n      team = \"dev\";\n      console.log(chalk.dim(\"  Piped mode — defaulting to t