{"type":"message","id":"966b6e73","parentId":"6f5cbbe7","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:39:13.522Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The agent files exist! The agent source files are present in `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-backend/`. So why does the script say \"No source agent files found\"?\n\nLet me check if maybe the script was run from a different CWD. The script in `install.sh` runs:\n```bash\ncd \"$INSTALL_DIR\" && git pull ...\n```\nThen:\n```bash\nnode bin/ahv-setup.js --team \"$team\"\n```\n\nSo CWD would be `$INSTALL_DIR` which is `~/.openclaw-setup`. And in the script:\n```javascript\nconst searchPaths = [\n  path.join(process.env.OPENCLAW_HOME || \"\", \"workspaces2\", \"v4-ecosystem-review\", agentId),\n  path.join(process.env.HOME || \"\", \".openclaw\", \"workspaces2\", \"v4-ecosystem-review\", agentId),\n  path.join(process.env.HOME || \"\", \".openclaw\", \"workspaces\", agentId),\n];\n```\n\nWhen `OPENCLAW_HOME` isn't set, it's checking `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-backend/`, which should work. But if the script is running from a different directory or if the path resolution is off, it might not find the files even though they exist.\n\nLooking at the backup path `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-1776256684863.json` in the user's output, I can see the setup is running from `/root/.openclaw`. The search path construction looks correct—it's joining `process.env.HOME || \"\"` with `.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-backend`, so `~/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-backend` should be found. Let me check the `coreFiles` definition to see what files it's actually looking for.","thinkingSignature":"f5a175f885f1f2698c195f9df5e8acdebf0f67164d6b41d22c4e0336bd9b0903"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_396zq2wm2t2w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"coreFiles\\|searchPaths\\|COPYRIGHT\\|wsDir\\|HOME.*workspace\" /root/