{"type":"message","id":"fcf607b6","parentId":"77bbd8d9","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:40:07.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"None of the common keys work. The data is encrypted but I can't decrypt it with common keys. This means the `skills.pack` was created with a different key that we don't know.\n\nThis is a serious issue — the skills pack is unreadable with the current script. We need to figure out the actual key, OR we need to download the skills pack from the GitHub repo (which should have the matching key).\n\nSince we can't `git fetch` from the origin, let me try a different approach. Maybe the skills pack was created from the current agent files and we can figure out the key by:\n1. Taking a known file content\n2. Encrypting it with the script's XOR function\n\n\n3. Comparing with the pack\n\nOr maybe the real issue is that `skills.pack` is actually unused in the main install flow — it's referenced in the bin script but might not be part of the actual download process. Let me trace through what the user actually gets when they run the curl command to see if `skills.pack` is even part of the delivery mechanism.","thinkingSignature":"794a0f88b6e2c167d9c9aa6a6f5ace73b92b5421044ceac1dcf1a74ca39c806a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l382i1ao2qup_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what repo the setup clones\ngrep \"REPO\\|github\\|clone\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/install.sh | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l382i1ao2qup_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check the install dir on disk vs repo\nls ~/.openclaw-setup/bin/ 2>/dev/null && echo \"EXISTS\" || echo \"NOT EXISTS\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":144,"output":336,"cacheRead":73475,"cacheWrite":828,"totalTokens":74783,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","ti