{"type":"message","id":"31617f6c","parentId":"05bfc3d7","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:43:16.709Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The paths resolve correctly! The second search path should find the files. So why did the user's run say \"No source agent files found\"?\n\nWait — maybe the issue is that the user's run happened BEFORE my fix (the current script). Let me check when the setup was run vs when I made changes.\n\nLooking at the user output:\n- The backup file is: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-1776256684863.json`\n- Timestamp: 1776256684863 = April 15, 2026, 12:18 UTC\n\nWait, 1776256684863 is April 15, 2026 12:18 UTC? No, 1776256684 is April 15, 2026... let me recalculate.\n \nI'm getting confused about the timestamp conversion. Let me work through this more carefully — Unix timestamps for April 2026 should be around 1.77 trillion milliseconds, so that backup timestamp of 1776256684863 milliseconds converts to about April 15, 2026 around 8:58 PM UTC, which doesn't match the user's output showing 12:18 UTC.\n\nWait, the math is off by a factor of 1000 — the backup file is actually from April 15, 2026 at 12:18 UTC. I need to check when I committed the install script and setup.js changes to see if they happened before or after the backup file was created.\n\nLooking at the git log, the install script was committed at 12:30, which is after the backup timestamp of 12:18, so that part checks out.\n\nBut the ahv-setup.js changes went in earlier commits — the confluence fix at 12:04 and the pipe mode fix at 12:30 — yet the unpack error message in the user's output doesn't match what's in the current version of the script, which suggests they might be running an older version.\n\nLooking at the actual unpackSkills function, I see it's handling the decryption key and decompressing the skill files, then writing them out with the right permissions.\n\nWait, but the old version had the correct formula too — it used the same XO