{"type":"message","id":"b4f1c970","parentId":"af82f1aa","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:50:00.523Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The committed skills.pack (HEAD=7d79e2c) has `key=None` and 35 entries, while the local file has `key=ahv-openclaw-2026` and 36 entries. They're different! And neither matches what the script expects.\n\nLet me look at what the committed version has vs what the script expects:\n\nCommitted version: `key=None`, `entries=35`Local version: `key=ahv-openclaw-2026`, `entries=36`Script expects: `key=ahv-openclaw-2026`\n\nThe local file was modified/regenerated at some point. \n\nSo the real issue is that the committed pack doesn't have the encryption key in the manifest like the script expects, which is why decryption fails. The local file was regenerated with the proper key and entry count, but then I accidentally overwrote it with the committed version that has `key=None`. I need to regenerate the local file with the correct encryption key to match what the script is looking for. the fix was to add the decryption XOR formula `^ (i & 0xff)`. This is already in the current script.\n\nSo the issue might be:\n1. The committed skills.pack (HEAD=7d79e2c) was created with a different key or different encryption method\n2. The current script uses the correct key `ahv-openclaw-2026` with XOR formula\n3. But the local skills.pack file (that I overwrote with `git checkout HEAD -- ahv-openclaw-setup/skills.pack`) was a DIFFERENT file from the original committed one!\n\nWait, I did `git checkout HEAD -- ahv-openclaw-setup/skills.pack` to RESTORE it, but the local file already had `key=ahv-openclaw-2026` and 36 entries. If HEAD has `key=None` and 35 entries, then my checkout would have OVERWRITTEN the local file with the wrong version. That's the real problem—the local pack had the correct encryption key, but I replaced it with a committed version that doesn't have it at all. I need to restore the local file with the proper key and entry count. I see the issue now—the local version with the encryption key and 36 entries is the correct one that was here before I ran the checkout, so I need to restore it instead of the committed HEAD version that has different metadata.","thinkingSignature":"1be3dd0a20f234301c4cb16ce6fff4ab150cb4a66abb4929a65690b0950f6a05"},{"type":"text","text":"\nSetup repo có 2 versions khác nhau. Local pack có `key=ahv-openclaw-2026` nhưng HEAD commit lại có `key=None`. Restore về local đúng:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gql52x4uxpie_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && python3 -c \"\nimport json, base64, zlib\n\n# Use local pack (has key=ahv-openclaw-2026, 36 entries)\nd = json.load(open('skills.pack'))\nbuf = base64.b64decode(d['payloads'][d['manifest'][0]['file']])\nkey = b'ahv-openclaw-2026'\ndec = bytes(buf[i] ^ key[i % len(key)] ^ (i & 0xff) for i in range(len(buf)))\ntext = zlib.decompress(dec)\nprint('Local pack decrypt SUCCESS:', text[:80])\nprint('Local entries:', len(d['manifest']))\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":179,"output":724,"cacheRead":158194,"cacheWrite":358,"totalTokens":159455,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776257383198,"responseId":"062ebc69092baedd7c05dba444a54a5c"}}
