{"type":"message","id":"53f14b68","parentId":"571093c7","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:51:53.489Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture! The setup repo's `HEAD` (commit `8404206`) has a VERY DIFFERENT config structure:\n- HEAD: `['env', 'models', 'agents', 'channels', 'bindings', 'mcp', 'gateway']`\n- Local: `['meta', 'env', 'browser', 'auth', 'models', 'agents', 'accounts', 'mcpServers', 'session', 'tools', 'skills']`\n\nThese are completely different config schemas! The local configs are from the WORKSPACE repo (v4-ecosystem-review), not from the setup repo!\n\n\nSo the local `configs/team-dev.json` was copied from the workspace, not from the actual setup repo. I copied it there earlier when I ran `cp` commands from the workspace. The committed HEAD version is the actual original setup repo config with the correct structure. So my \"fix\" actually overwrote the correct setup config with the workspace version—that's the bug I need to revert.","thinkingSignature":"3a6d287f0b9a13a327b18df3c2a83901315e6ba27545e5ee1baa9c6558927ac6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jxvgc9ifagqg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && git show 8404206:configs/team-dev.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint('Keys:', list(d.keys()))\nprint('mcpServers:', list(d.get('mcpServers',{}).keys()) if 'mcpServers' in d else 'N/A')\nprint('mcp:', list(d.get('mcp',{}).keys()) if 'mcp' in d else 'N/A')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":362,"output":351,"cacheRead":162772,"cacheWrite":641,"totalTokens":164126,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776257504343,"responseId":"062ebce19a3e9a6063b360aa8cb67332"}}
