{"type":"message","id":"f5d312ab","parentId":"dcc0b769","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:38:38.908Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the skills directory structure is:\n`~/.openclaw/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md`\n\nThe manifest should have entries like:\n- `prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md`\n\nAnd the unpack script strips the `{agent}/` prefix and writes to `~/.openclaw/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md`.BUT currently, the manifest has entries like:\n- `prompt-optimizer/skills/prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md`\n- `senior-backend/skills/senior-backend/SKILL.md`\n\nThe extra `skills/` in the path is wrong. The pack was created with incorrect manifest entries. The correct manifest entries should be:\n\n\n- `{agent}/SKILL.md`\n\nI need to rebuild the skills pack with the correct manifest entries, and the unpack script should strip the `{agent}/` prefix and write to `~/.openclaw/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md` without adding an extra `skills/` directory. Looking at the script more carefully, I see it's constructing the file path by joining `destDir`, \"skills\", and the `relativePath`, so I need to verify the current unpack logic is handling the prefix stripping correctly.\n\nThe script strips `{agent}/` from entries like `prompt-optimizer/skills/prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md` to get `skills/prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md`, then writes to `~/.openclaw/skills/skills/prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md` — which is still wrong. The fix is to have the manifest contain `{agent}/SKILL.md` instead, so after stripping the prefix I get just `SKILL.md` and the final path becomes `~/.openclaw/skills/prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md`. I'm realizing the manifest might have been created with incorrect paths, but I can't decrypt it to verify since the key might not be `ahv-openclaw-2026`. Rather than spend time trying to decrypt, I'll just rebuild the entire skills pack from scratch with the correct manifest entries—stripping the leading agent directory to get clean paths like `{agent}/SKILL.md`.","thinkingSig