{"type":"message","id":"6f702d78","parentId":"2a3b74b0","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:39:44.573Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture:\n\n1. The original pack (efb7680) has 36 entries with paths like `{agent}/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md`\n2. The current broken pack (that was written to disk) has 1 entry with a DIFFERENT format\n3. The unpack script's `relativePath = entry.file.slice(agentPrefix.length)` gives `skills/agile-product-owner/SKILL.md`\n4. Then `filePath = path.join(destDir, \"skills\", relativePath)` gives `destDir/skills/skills/...` ❌\n\nSo the ORIGINAL pack (efb7680) also has the double-nesting problem! The skills would be unpacked to `~/.openclaw/skills/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md` which is WRONG.\n\n\nThe real solution is to strip both the agent prefix and the `skills/` directory component so the final path becomes `~/.openclaw/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md`. I'm modifying the unpack logic to extract the relative path after removing the agent directory, then use that directly without adding an extra `skills/` layer on top.\n\nWriting the corrected unpack script... So the original pack was actually created with the wrong manifest format—those entries shouldn't have the `skills/` directory in them at all. I need to rebuild it from scratch with the correct structure where each file path is just `{agent}/FILENAME.md`, then update the unpack script to handle the new format properly.","thinkingSignature":"0be492d3354f66258d505664ab889026c42df47f89ec324c96d5d4346521c575"},{"type":"text","text":"Manifest gốc cũng bị sai path — `skills/` thừa. Rebuild đúng format và fix unpack script:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_clgxgguq559h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport os, json, zlib, base64\n\nAGENTS = ['agile-product-owner','clean-code','code-reviewer','coding-standards','content-strategy',\n  'database-reviewer','database-schema-designer','epic-design','harness-optimizer',\n  'market-intelligence','master-orchestrator','performance-optimizer','planner',\n  'playwright-pro','product-marketing-context','product-strategy','prompt-optimizer',\n  'realistic-seeder','refactor-cleaner','security-reviewer','senior-architect',\n  'senior-backend','senior-devops','senior-frontend','senior-qa','senior-security',\n  'seo-audit','shadcn-expert','stitch-design','stitch-loop','typescript-reviewer',\n  'ui-design-system','ui-ux-pro-max']\n\nSKILL_KEY = \"ahv-openclaw-2026\"\nSKILL_KEY_BYTES = SKILL_KEY.encode()\n\ndef encrypt(data_bytes):\n    # Match the JS: XOR with key + (i & 0xff), then zlib compress\n    out = bytearray(len(data_bytes))\n    for i in range(len(data_bytes)):\n        out[i] = data_bytes[i] ^ SKILL_KEY_BYTES[i % len(SKILL_KEY_BYTES)] ^ (i & 0xff)\n    compressed = zlib.compress(bytes(out))\n    return base64.b64encode(compressed).decode()\n\nmanifest = []\npayloads = {}\n\nfor agent in sorted(AGENTS):\n    src_dir = f'agent-defs/{agent}' if os.path.isdir(f'agent-defs/{agent}') else f'agent-templates/{agent}'\n    if not os.path.isdir(src_dir):\n        continue\n    for fname in sorted(os.listdir(src_dir)):\n        fpath = os.path.join(src_dir, fname)\n        if not os.path.isfile(fpath):\n            continue\n        with open(fpath, 'rb') as f:\n            content = f.read()\n        # Correct path: \"{agent}/{filename}\" — e.g. \"senior-backend/SOUL.md\"\n        entry_path = f'{agent}/{fname}'\n        manifest.append({'file': entry_path, 'size': len(content)})\n        payloads[entry_path] = encrypt(content)\n\nprint(f'Generated {len(manifest)} entries')\n# Test decrypt\ntest_entry = manifest[0]['file']\nbuf = base64.b64decode(payloads[test_entry])\ndec = bytearray(len(buf))\nfor i in range(len(buf)):\n    dec[i] = buf[i] ^ SKILL_KEY_BYTES[i % len(SKILL_KEY_BYTES)] ^ (i & 0xff)\ntext = zlib.decompress(bytes(dec))\nprint(f'Decrypt test: OK! \"{text[:50]}\"')\nprint('Sample entries:')\nfor e in manifest[:10]:\n    print(f'  {e[\"file\"]}')\n\npack = {\n    'version': '1.0',\n    'packedAt': '2026-04-16T00:00:00.000Z',\n    'fileCount': len(manifest),\n    'key': SKILL_KEY,\n    'manifest': manifest,\n    'payloads': payloads\n}\nwith open('skills.pack', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(pack, f, indent=2)\nprint(f'\\n✅ Pack saved: {os.path.getsize(\"skills.pack\")/1024:.1f} KB, {len(manifest)} entries')\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":338,"output":1110,"cacheRead":136572,"cacheWrite":1474,"totalTokens":139494,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776303563881,"responseId":"062f70cd6a466b05aab22db6bf20769e"}}
